== Tofinu ==
Tofinu people probably emigrated from Togo during the 18th Century during the Adja (Fon) war. They settled around the '''Nokue lake''' (South of present Benin) and live above the lake water in houses on pile foundations.
Village like '''Canvié''' protected them against the Fon, whose believings forbade to go above water. It is now a touristic place.
Tofinu's main activity is fishing and they have created some acquaculture. 
